nch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"resilient-squishing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01DwXRF3kFp22MXzv3myNiq9\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_012iCGPykzRgCRmyAcGmDtaS\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/.claude/plans/resilient-squishing-fern.md\",\"content\":\"# Real-Time Turbopuffer Indexing via Cloudflare Queue\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCheckpoints are indexed in Turbopuffer for search (vector + BM25). Currently this only happens via the backfill script. When new checkpoints arrive via GitHub webhooks, they need to be indexed in Turbopuffer in real-time. The indexing must be async and non-blocking to the webhook processing pipeline.\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\nAdd a new `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE` Cloudflare Queue. After checkpoint data is upserted into PlanetScale (in both `processSessionsPushEvent` and `processCommitPushEvent`), send a lightweight message to the queue with the checkpoint IDs and repo ID. A new queue consumer embeds the search text via OpenAI and upserts vectors to Turbopuffer.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Action | Description |\\n|------|--------|-------------|\\n| `api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts` | **Create** | Message type, type guard, batch processor |\\n| `api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts` | **Modify** | Add `indexCheckpoints()` function (embed + upsert) |\\n| `api/src/env.ts` | **Modify** | Add `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE?: Queue` binding |\\n| `api/wrangler.jsonc` | **Modify** | Add queue producer + consumer (staging & production) |\\n| `api/src/index.ts` | **Modify** | Add queue consumer branch for search index messages |\\n| `api/src/lib/webhook/processing.ts` | **Modify** | Enqueue after upsert in both push event handlers |\\n\\n## Implementation Details\\n\\n### 1. Message Type & Queue Consumer (`api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts`)\\n\\nFollow the existing `RepoSyncMessage` / `UserRepoSyncMessage` pattern:\\n\\n```typescript\\nexport interface SearchIndexMessage {\\n  repoId: string;\\n  checkpointIds: string[];\\n  queuedAt: string;\\n}\\n\\nexport function isSearchIndexMessage(msg: unknown): msg is SearchIndexMessage { ... }\\n\\nexport async function processSearchIndexBatch(\\n  batch: MessageBatch<SearchIndexMessage>,\\n  env: Env,\\n): Promise<void> { ... }\\n```\\n\\n**Batch processor flow:**\\n1. For each message, fetch checkpoint + commit data from PlanetScale via `db.checkpoints.getByIds(repoId, checkpointIds)`\\n2. Build search text per checkpoint (prompt, commit message, files touched — same as backfill's `buildSearchText`)\\n3. Call `indexCheckpoints()` from turbopuffer.ts (embeds text via OpenAI, upserts to Turbopuffer)\\n4. On success: `msg.ack()`. On transient failure: `msg.retry()`. On missing API keys: `msg.ack()` with warning log (graceful skip).\\n\\n### 2. Turbopuffer Indexing Function (`api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts`)\\n\\nAdd an `indexCheckpoints()` function that replicates the backfill logic:\\n\\n```typescript\\nexport async function indexCheckpoints(\\n  turbopufferApiKey: string,\\n  openaiApiKey: string,\\n  repoId: string,\\n  checkpoints: Array<{\\n    checkpoint_id: string;\\n    branch: string;\\n    agent: string;\\n    commit_author_username: string | null;\\n    created_at: string | null;\\n    commit_sha: string | null;\\n    commit_message: string | null;\\n    prompt: string | null;\\n    files_touched: string[] | null;\\n  }>,\\n): Promise<number>\\n```\\n\\n- Builds search text per checkpoint (same format as backfill)\\n- Batch-embeds via OpenAI (`text-embedding-3-small`, 1536 dims)\\n- Upserts to Turbopuffer namespace `checkpoints-{repoId}` with same attributes as backfill\\n- Uses sequential integer IDs derived from a hash of `checkpoint_id` to stay consistent\\n- Returns count of indexed checkpoints\\n\\n### 3. Env Binding (`api/src/env.ts`)\\n\\nAdd optional queue binding:\\n```typescript\\nSEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE?: Queue;  // Optional — indexing is skipped if not configured\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Wrangler Queue Config (`api/wrangler.jsonc`)\\n\\nAdd to both staging and production:\\n```jsonc\\n// Producer\\n{ \\\"binding\\\": \\\"SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE\\\", \\\"queue\\\": \\\"<env>-api-search-index\\\" }\\n\\n// Consumer\\n{\\n  \\\"queue\\\": \\\"<env>-api-search-index\\\",\\n  \\\"max_retries\\\": 3,\\n  \\\"max_batch_size\\\": 10,\\n  \\\"max_batch_timeout\\\": 5\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Queue Consumer Routing (`api/src/index.ts`)\\n\\nAdd a new branch in the `queue()` handler, before the unknown-message fallback:\\n\\n```typescript\\n} else if (firstMessage && isSearchIndexMessage(firstMessage)) {\\n  await processSearchIndexBatch(\\n    batch as MessageBatch<SearchIndexMessage>,\\n    env,\\n  );\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 6. Enqueue After Upsert (`api/src/lib/webhook/processing.ts`)\\n\\n**In `processSessionsPushEvent()`** (line ~965, after `db.checkpoints.upsertBatch` succeeds):\\n```typescript\\nif (env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE) {\\n  await env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE.send({\\n    repoId: repoRecord.id,\\n    checkpointIds,\\n    queuedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\\n  } satisfies SearchIndexMessage);\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**In `processCommitPushEvent()`** (line ~1220, after `db.checkpoints.upsertCommitBatch` succeeds):\\n```typescript\\nif (env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE) {\\n  const ids = checkpointCommits.map((c) => c.checkpointId);\\n  await env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE.send({\\n    repoId: repoRecord.id,\\n    checkpointIds: ids,\\n    queuedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\\n  } satisfies SearchIndexMessage);\\n}\\n```\\n\\nBoth are fire-and-forget — if the queue send fails, the webhook processing still succeeds. The checkpoint will get indexed on the next backfill run.\\n\\n## Key Design Decisions\\n\\n- **Optional queue binding** (`SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE?`): Indexing is purely additive — if the queue or API keys aren't configured, everything else works normally\\n- **Reuse `getByIds()`**: The queue consumer fetches full checkpoint data from PlanetScale rather than passing it in the message. This keeps messages small and ensures we index the latest data\\n- **Same vector format as backfill**: Attributes and text construction match `backfill-search.ts` exactly so results are consistent\\n- **`msg.ack()` on missing API keys**: Don't retry messages that will never succeed. Log a warning instead.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Deploy queue: `wrangler queues create partialto-api-search-index` (staging)\\n2. Set secrets: `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` and `OPENAI_API_KEY` via `wrangler secret put`\\n3. Push a commit with an `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer to a repo with the GitHub App installed\\n4. Check worker logs for `[search-index-queue]` entries showing successful indexing\\n5. Search for the new checkpoint via the search endpoint\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":707,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":124235,\"output_tokens\":1939,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":707,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYiaKs66yZCVZWo37wd8j\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"b90f6a68-b712-42ee-8836-0d8c3d041dec\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:16:12.901Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b90f6a68-b712-42ee-8836-0d8c3d041dec\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"b3a25300-460d-43d2-8f54-c13ecfe5387c\",\"version\":\"2.1.56\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"resilient-squishing-fern\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"<tool_use_error>File has not been read yet. Read it first before writing to it.</tool_use_error>\",\"is_error\":true,\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_012iCGPykzRgCRmyAcGmDtaS\"}]},\"uuid\":\"ce836545-e890-4627-b257