 (required, non-empty)\\n    73→2. Check repo access (reuse existing `checkRepoAccess()` helper)\\n    74→3. If `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` not set, return 503\\n    75→4. Call `searchCheckpoints()` with `repoRecord.id`, query, and optional branch filter\\n    76→5. Get the `checkpoint_id` list from results\\n    77→6. Fetch full checkpoint data from PlanetScale using existing `db.checkpoints.getByIds(repoId, checkpointIds)`\\n    78→7. Map through existing `mapCheckpointToInfo()` to build response\\n    79→8. Return in same shape as the existing checkpoints endpoint for frontend compatibility\\n    80→\\n    81→**Auth**: Same `optionalAuth + rateLimitUnauthenticated` pattern as existing checkpoint routes.\\n    82→\\n    83→**Response**: Same `CheckpointsResponse` type so the frontend can render search results identically to the normal list.\\n    84→\\n    85→### 4. Frontend API Function (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/api.ts`)\\n    86→\\n    87→Add:\\n    88→```typescript\\n    89→export async function searchCheckpoints(\\n    90→  org: string, repo: string, query: string, branch?: string,\\n    91→): Promise<CheckpointsResponse> {\\n    92→  const params = new URLSearchParams({ q: query });\\n    93→  if (branch) params.set(\\\"branch\\\", branch);\\n    94→  return request<CheckpointsResponse>(\\n    95→    `/api/v1/cache/${org}/${repo}/checkpoints/search?${params.toString()}`\\n    96→  );\\n    97→}\\n    98→```\\n    99→\\n   100→Reuses the existing `CheckpointsResponse` type — no new response types needed.\\n   101→\\n   102→### 5. Frontend Hook (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/hooks/useCommitsQuery.ts`)\\n   103→\\n   104→Add:\\n   105→```typescript\\n   106→export function useSearchCheckpointsQuery(\\n   107→  org: string, repo: string, query: string, branch: string,\\n   108→) {\\n   109→  return useQuery<CheckpointsResponse>({\\n   110→    queryKey: [\\\"github\\\", \\\"checkpoints-search\\\", org, repo, query, branch],\\n   111→    queryFn: () => searchCheckpoints(org, repo, query, branch),\\n   112→    enabled: query.trim().length > 0,\\n   113→    staleTime: 30_000,\\n   114→    placeholderData: (prev) => prev, // keep previous results while fetching\\n   115→  });\\n   116→}\\n   117→```\\n   118→\\n   119→### 6. Frontend Page (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/pages/CheckpointsPage.tsx`)\\n   120→\\n   121→Replace the client-side filter block (lines 82-95) with debounced API search:\\n   122→\\n   123→- Add `useEffect`-based debounce (300ms) on `searchQuery` → `debouncedQuery`\\n   124→- Call `useSearchCheckpointsQuery(org, repo, debouncedQuery, branch)`\\n   125→- When `debouncedQuery` is non-empty, use search results; otherwise use normal checkpoint list\\n   126→- Show subtle loading indicator while search is in flight\\n   127→- Update \\\"No matching checkpoints\\\" empty state to work with search results\\n   128→\\n   129→Key changes:\\n   130→- Remove: the `allCheckpoints.filter(...)` client-side logic\\n   131→- Add: `debouncedQuery` state + `useEffect` debounce\\n   132→- Add: `useSearchCheckpointsQuery` hook call\\n   133→- Modify: `checkpoints` derivation to branch on `isSearchActive`\\n   134→\\n   135→## Verification\\n   136→\\n   137→1. Set `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` via `wrangler secret put TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` for staging\\n   138→2. Start API locally with `wrangler dev` — verify search endpoint:\\n   139→   ```\\n   140→   curl \\\"http://localhost:8787/api/v1/cache/entireio/cli/checkpoints/search?q=authentication&branch=main\\\"\\n   141→   ```\\n   142→3. Start frontend locally — test search UX:\\n   143→   - Debounced API calls (no call until 300ms after typing stops)\\n   144→   - Results render in the same ListView format\\n   145→   - Empty query shows normal checkpoint list\\n   146→   - \\\"No results\\\" state for queries with no matches\\n   147→   - Previous results stay visible while new search is loading\\n   148→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"f9a71215-2de9-4b42-9237-a578066a9b21\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:16:15.938Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/.claude/plans/resilient-squishing-fern.md\",\"content\":\"# Wire Up Checkpoint Search via Turbopuffer\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCheckpoints have been backfilled into Turbopuffer (namespace `checkpoints-{repo_id}`) with embeddings and attributes. The frontend currently does client-side string matching over prompts, commit messages, and authors. We need to:\\n\\n1. Add a search API endpoint that queries Turbopuffer\\n2. Replace the frontend's client-side filtering with API-driven search\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\n- **API**: Direct `fetch()` calls to Turbopuffer REST API from the Cloudflare Worker (no new runtime dependencies)\\n- **Frontend**: Replace client-side filter entirely — when search input is non-empty, call the search endpoint; when empty, show the normal checkpoint list\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Action | Description |\\n|------|--------|-------------|\\n| `api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts` | **Create** | Thin Turbopuffer REST client (query function) |\\n| `api/src/env.ts` | **Modify** | Add optional `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` to `Env` interface |\\n| `api/src/routes/cache.ts` | **Modify** | Add `GET /:org/:repo/checkpoints/search` endpoint |\\n| `frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/api.ts` | **Modify** | Add `searchCheckpoints()` fetch function + response type |\\n| `frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/hooks/useCommitsQuery.ts` | **Modify** | Add `useSearchCheckpointsQuery()` hook |\\n| `frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/pages/CheckpointsPage.tsx` | **Modify** | Wire search input to API query, replace client-side filter |\\n\\n## Implementation Details\\n\\n### 1. Turbopuffer REST Client (`api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts`)\\n\\nThin wrapper around Turbopuffer's REST API using `fetch()`. No SDK needed.\\n\\n```typescript\\nexport interface TurbopufferSearchResult {\\n  checkpoint_id: string;\\n  // other attributes returned for convenience\\n}\\n\\nexport async function searchCheckpoints(\\n  apiKey: string,\\n  repoId: string,\\n  query: string,\\n  filters?: { branch?: string },\\n  limit?: number,\\n): Promise<TurbopufferSearchResult[]>\\n```\\n\\n**Turbopuffer REST endpoint**: `POST https://api.turbopuffer.com/v1/vectors/checkpoints-{repo_id}/query`\\n\\n**Request body** — use BM25 full-text search on the `text` attribute + optional attribute filters:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"top_k\\\": 50,\\n  \\\"rank_by\\\": [\\\"text\\\", \\\"BM25\\\", \\\"search query here\\\"],\\n  \\\"filters\\\": {\\n    \\\"branch\\\": [[\\\"Eq\\\", \\\"main\\\"]]\\n  },\\n  \\\"include_attributes\\\": [\\\"checkpoint_id\\\"]\\n}\\n```\\n\\nReturns `checkpoint_id` values which we use to fetch full checkpoint data from PlanetScale.\\n\\n### 2. Env Update (`api/src/env.ts`)\\n\\nAdd `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY?: string` as optional to the `Env` interface. Not added to `REQUIRED_ENV_VARS` since search is an optional feature — the endpoint returns 503 if the key is missing.\\n\\n### 3. Search API Endpoint (`api/src/routes/cache.ts`)\\n\\nNew route on `repoRoutes`: `GET /:org/:repo/checkpoints/search?q=<query>&branch=<branch>`\\n\\n**Flow**:\\n1. Validate `q` param (required, non-empty)\\n2. Check repo access (reuse existing `checkRepoAccess()` helper)\\n3. If `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` not set, return 503\\n4. Call `searchCheckpoints()` with `repoRecord.id`, query, and optional branch filter\\n5. Get the `checkpoint_id` list from results\\n6. Fetch full checkpoint data from PlanetScale using existing `db.checkpoints.getByIds(repoId, checkpointIds)`\\n7. Map through existing `mapCheckpointToInfo()` to build response\\n8. Return in same shape as the existing checkpoints endpoint for frontend compatibility\\n\\n**Auth**: Same `optionalAuth + rateLimitUnauthenticated` pattern as existing checkpoint routes.\\n\\n**Response**: Same `CheckpointsResponse` type so the frontend can render search results identically to the normal list.\\n\\n### 4. Frontend API Function (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/api.ts`)\\n\\nAdd:\\n```typescript\\nexport async function searchCheckpoints(\\n  org: string, repo: string, query: string, branch?: string,\\n): Promise<CheckpointsResponse> {\\n  const params = new URLSearchParams({ q: query });\\n  if (branch) params.set(\\\"branch\\\", branch);\\n  return request<CheckpointsResponse>(\\n    `/api/v1/cache/${org}/${repo}/checkpoints/search?${params.toString()}`\\n  );\\n}\\n```\\n\\nReuses the existing `CheckpointsResponse` type — no new response types needed.\\n\\n### 5. Frontend Hook (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/hooks/useCommitsQuery.ts`)\\n\\nAdd:\\n```typescript\\nexport function useSearchCheckpointsQuery(\\n  org: string, repo: string, query: string, branch: string,\\n) {\\n  return useQuery<CheckpointsResponse>({\\n    queryKey: [\\\"github\\\", \\\"checkpoints-search\\\", org, repo, query, branch],\\n    queryFn: () => searchCheckpoints(org, repo, query, branch),\\n    enabled: query.trim().length > 0,\\n    staleTime: 30_000,\\n    placeholderData: (prev) => prev, // keep previous results while fetching\\n  });\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 6. Frontend Page (`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/pages/CheckpointsPage.tsx`)\\n\\nReplace the client-side filter block (lines 82-95) with debounced API search:\\n\\n- Add `useEffect`-based debounce (300ms) on `searchQuery` → `debouncedQuery`\\n- Call `useSearchCheckpointsQuery(org, repo, debouncedQuery, branch)`\\n- When `debouncedQuery` is non-empty, use search results; otherwise use normal checkpoint list\\n- Show subtle loading indicator while search is in flight\\n- Update \\\"No matching checkpoints\\\" empty state to work with search results\\n\\nKey changes:\\n- Remove: the `allCheckpoints.filter(...)` client-side logic\\n- Add: `debouncedQuery` state + `useEffect` debounce\\n- Add: `useSearchCheckpointsQuery` hook call\\n- Modify: `checkpoints` derivation to branch on `isSearchActive`\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Set `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` via `wrangler secret put TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` for staging\\n2. Start API locally with `wrangler dev` — verify search endpoint:\\n   ```\\n   curl \\\"http://localhost:8787/api/v1/cache/entireio/cli/checkpoints/search?q=authentication&branch=main\\\"\\n   ```\\n3. Start frontend locally — test search UX:\\n   - Debounced API calls (no call until 300ms after typing stops)\\n   - Results render in the same ListView format\\n   - Empty query shows normal checkpoint list\\n   - \\\"No results\\\" state for queries with no matches\\n   - Previous results stay visible while new search is loading\\n\",\"numLines\":148,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":148}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"d1d83bef-69ca-49e8-85b4-da060adcb426\"}\n{\"type\":\"file-history-snapshot\",\"messageId\":\"779e7d52-e453-425b-b70b-37e0862e97a2\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"ea24ba89-dd2b-4696-b1be-bc20d0cf806f\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"cfe3cf9f80a2a907@v6\",\"version\":6,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T06:11:39.083Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/src/env.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"71fd94ed958a53c5@v3\",\"version\":3,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T06:07:18.453Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/src/routes/cache.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"0cd1f375b09f4cb1@v3\",\"version\":3,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T06:07:18.453Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/api.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"50b3fa718386220d@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T05:50:59.212Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/hooks/useCommitsQuery.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"a48dc6b2b69f4956@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T05:50:59.213Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/pages/CheckpointsPage.tsx\":{\"backupFileName\":\"653a7ef579f206c7@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T05:50:59.213Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/pages/CheckpointsPage.test.tsx\":{\"backupFileName\":\"4ecf8b82ea273e2f@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T05:50:59.213Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/.claude/plans/resilient-squishing-fern.md\":{\"backupFileName\":\"cdbadcbe5f5d68a2@v1\",\"version\":1,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T19:16:46.568Z\"}},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:13:34.763Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":true}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"f9a71215-2de9-4b42-9237-a578066a9b21\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"b3a25300-460d-43d2-8f54-c13ecfe5387c\",\"version\":\"2.1.56\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"resilient-squishing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01LMk5rjE1VsMG6GTTGkcWhN\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Xos8DcntMT9BDLxsmnwRQ9\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/.claude/plans/resilient-squishing-fern.md\",\"content\":\"# Real-Time Turbopuffer Indexing via Cloudflare Queue\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCheckpoints are indexed in Turbopuffer for search. Currently indexing only happens via the backfill script. When new checkpoints arrive via GitHub webhooks, they need to be indexed in Turbopuffer in real-time. The indexing must be async and non-blocking to the webhook processing pipeline, using Cloudflare Queues (already set up for other flows).\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\nAdd a new `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE` Cloudflare Queue. After checkpoint data is upserted into PlanetScale (in both `processSessionsPushEvent` and `processCommitPushEvent`), send a lightweight message to the queue. A new queue consumer fetches checkpoint data from PlanetScale, embeds search text via OpenAI, and upserts vectors to Turbopuffer.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Action | Description |\\n|------|--------|-------------|\\n| `api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts` | **Create** | Message type, type guard, batch processor |\\n| `api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts` | **Modify** | Add `indexCheckpoints()` function (embed + upsert) |\\n| `api/src/env.ts` | **Modify** | Add optional `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE?: Queue` |\\n| `api/wrangler.jsonc` | **Modify** | Add queue producer + consumer (staging & production) |\\n| `api/src/index.ts` | **Modify** | Add queue consumer branch for search index messages |\\n| `api/src/lib/webhook/processing.ts` | **Modify** | Enqueue after upsert in both push event handlers |\\n\\n## Implementation Details\\n\\n### 1. Search Index Queue (`api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts`)\\n\\nFollow existing `RepoSyncMessage` / `UserRepoSyncMessage` pattern from `repo-sync-queue.ts` and `user-repo-sync.ts`.\\n\\n```typescript\\nexport interface SearchIndexMessage {\\n  repoId: string;\\n  checkpointIds: string[];\\n  queuedAt: string;\\n}\\n\\nexport function isSearchIndexMessage(msg: unknown): msg is SearchIndexMessage { ... }\\n\\nexport async function processSearchIndexBatch(\\n  batch: MessageBatch<SearchIndexMessage>,\\n  env: Env,\\n): Promise<void> { ... }\\n```\\n\\n**Batch processor flow per message:**\\n1. Early return if `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` or `OPENAI_API_KEY` missing — `msg.ack()` + warning log\\n2. Fetch checkpoint + commit data from PlanetScale via `db.checkpoints.getByIds(repoId, checkpointIds)`\\n3. Build search text per checkpoint (same format as `buildSearchText()` in backfill script)\\n4. Call `indexCheckpoints()` from turbopuffer.ts\\n5. Success → `msg.ack()`, transient failure → `msg.retry()`\\n\\nLogging follows `[search-index-queue]` prefix pattern, with batch metrics matching `repo-sync-queue.ts`.\\n\\n### 2. Turbopuffer Indexing Function (`api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts`)\\n\\nAdd `indexCheckpoints()` alongside existing `searchCheckpoints()`:\\n\\n```typescript\\nexport async function indexCheckpoints(\\n  turbopufferApiKey: string,\\n  openaiApiKey: string,\\n  repoId: string,\\n  checkpoints: Array<{\\n    checkpoint_id: string;\\n    branch: string | null;\\n    agent: string | null;\\n    commit_author_username: string | null;\\n    created_at: string | null;\\n    commit_sha: string | null;\\n    commit_message: string | null;\\n    prompt: string | null;\\n    files_touched: string[] | null;\\n  }>,\\n): Promise<number>\\n```\\n\\n- Build search text: `Prompt: ...\\\\nCommit: ...\\\\nFiles: ...` (same as backfill `buildSearchText()`)\\n- Embed via OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` (1536 dims) — batch all texts in one call\\n- Upsert to Turbopuffer `POST /v1/vectors/checkpoints-{repoId}/upsert` with same attributes as backfill\\n- Use deterministic numeric IDs from checkpoint_id hash (consistent with potential re-indexing)\\n- Returns count of successfully indexed checkpoints\\n\\n### 3. Env Binding (`api/src/env.ts`)\\n\\n```typescript\\nSEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE?: Queue;  // Optional — indexing skipped if not configured\\n```\\n\\nOptional so existing environments without the queue continue working.\\n\\n### 4. Wrangler Config (`api/wrangler.jsonc`)\\n\\n**Staging (default):**\\n```jsonc\\n// In producers array:\\n{ \\\"binding\\\": \\\"SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE\\\", \\\"queue\\\": \\\"partialto-api-search-index\\\" }\\n// In consumers array:\\n{ \\\"queue\\\": \\\"partialto-api-search-index\\\", \\\"max_retries\\\": 3, \\\"max_batch_size\\\": 10, \\\"max_batch_timeout\\\": 5 }\\n```\\n\\n**Production (`env.production`):**\\n```jsonc\\n// In producers array:\\n{ \\\"binding\\\": \\\"SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE\\\", \\\"queue\\\": \\\"entireio-api-search-index\\\" }\\n// In consumers array:\\n{ \\\"queue\\\": \\\"entireio-api-search-index\\\", \\\"max_retries\\\": 3, \\\"max_batch_size\\\": 10, \\\"max_batch_timeout\\\": 5 }\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Queue Consumer Routing (`api/src/index.ts`)\\n\\nAdd new branch in `queue()` hand